---
/**
 * Shared “Tetris vs Tetris 50” comparison (used on /classic-games/tetris/ and /classic-games/tetris-50/).
 */
---

<section
  class="border-t border-slate-200/60 bg-slate-50/60"
  aria-labelledby="tetris-comparison-heading"
>
  <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 md:py-14">
    <h2
      id="tetris-comparison-heading"
      class="!text-xl sm:!text-2xl !font-bold !text-slate-900 !mb-4 !mt-0"
    >
      Tetris vs Tetris 50 — what is the difference?
    </h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-5 text-base leading-relaxed max-w-3xl m-0">
      Same board, same pieces, and the same controls and sounds. The
      <strong>win condition</strong> is what changes.
    </p>

    <div
      class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200/90 bg-white shadow-sm ring-1 ring-slate-900/5"
    >
      <table class="w-full min-w-[280px] text-left text-sm border-collapse">
        <caption class="sr-only">
          Comparison of Tetris and Tetris 50
        </caption>
        <thead>
          <tr
            class="bg-gradient-to-r from-slate-50 to-blue-50/30 border-b border-slate-200/80"
          >
            <th
              class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-800 w-1/3"
              scope="col"
            ></th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-800" scope="col">
              Tetris
            </th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-800" scope="col">
              Tetris 50
            </th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-slate-700">
          <tr class="border-b border-slate-100">
            <th
              class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600 align-top"
              scope="row"
            >
              Objective
            </th>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">
              Survive and score as high as you can. No fixed finish.
            </td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">
              Clear <strong>50 lines</strong> total to finish the run.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-slate-100">
            <th
              class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600 align-top"
              scope="row"
            >
              Success
            </th>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">
              Beating your score or a long, stable run.
            </td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">
              Hitting 50 lines cleared ends the run with a win (you still get
              a score for fun).
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-slate-100">
            <th
              class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600 align-top"
              scope="row"
            >
              Failure
            </th>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top" colspan="2">
              The same in both: if a new piece cannot spawn, the well is full
              — <strong>game over</strong>.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th
              class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600 align-top"
              scope="row"
            >
              Best for
            </th>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">Long sessions, chasing records.</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">
              A run with a clear “done” when you pass 50 lines.
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
